<h6 class="page-category">Children and Poverty</h6>
<h1>Famous Quotes About Children</h1>
        <p>People from every walk of life have something to say about children. These famous quotes about children show just how broad the spectrum is when it comes to people speaking up for children.</p>
        <p>No matter what others are saying, remember that <a href="/poverty/what-the-bible-says-about-children.htm">God views children as especially important</a> in His kingdom, and He has many of His own famous quotes about children.</p>
        <span class="h5">"A person's a person, no matter how small."
            <br>
            <span class="author">&mdash; Dr. Seuss</span></span>
        <p>
            <a href="/poverty/dr-seuss-flat-tummy-fweeps.htm">
                <amp-img layout="responsive" width="228" height="338" src="/Images/haitian-child-dr-seuss.jpg" class="paper" alt="A young Haitian boy peeks around something" title="What might it have sounded like if Dr. Seuss had written a story about children in poverty? Read The Flat-Tummy Fweeps by Compassion International"></amp-img>
            </a>
        </p>
        <p>What might it have sounded like if Dr. Seuss had written a story about children in poverty?</p>
        <blockquote>Now, the Fat-Tummy Fweeps had full tummies of food,
            <br> And the Flat-Tummy Fweeps had eyes that were glued
            <br> To the chowderly chow that could brighten their mood,
            <br> Which they had none of, and so were subdued.
            <br> Their tummies, you see, made noises at night...</blockquote>
        <p>Read the rest of <a href="/poverty/dr-seuss-flat-tummy-fweeps.htm"><em>The Flat-Tummy Fweeps</em></a></p>
        <span class="h5">"Adults are just outdated children."
<br>
<span class="author">&mdash; Dr. Seuss</span>
        <br>
        <br> "There can be no keener revelation of a society's soul than the way in which it treats its children."
        <br>
        <span class="author">&mdash; Nelson Mandela, Former President of South Africa</span></span>

        <span class="h5">"Children are likely to live up to what you believe of them."
<br>
<span class="author">&mdash; Lady Bird Johnson, Former First Lady of the United States</span></span>
        <amp-vimeo data-videoid="29501033" layout="responsive" width="500" height="281"></amp-vimeo>

        <p><em>Beguen Theus, a Compassion alumni, was elected to the Haitian parliament in 2011.</em></p>
        <span class="h5">"Children must be taught how to think, not what to think."
<br>
<span class="author">&mdash; Margaret Mead, cultural anthropologist</span>
        <br>
        <br> "The greatest legacy one can pass on to one's children and grandchildren is not money or other material things accumulated in one's life, but rather a legacy of character and faith."
        <br>
        <span class="author">&mdash; Billy Graham, evangelist</span>
        <br>
        <br> "We worry about what a child will become tomorrow, yet we forget that he is someone today."
        <br>
        <span class="author">&mdash; Stacia Tauscher, dancer and artist</span>
        <br>
        <br> "Children are not things to be molded, but are people to be unfolded."
        <br>
        <span class="author">&mdash; Jess Lair, author</span></span>
        <p>
            <amp-img layout="responsive" width="550" height="368" src="/Images/children-cement-molded-quotes.jpg" class="paper" alt="Two Ghanian children peek their eyes over a low cement wall" title="Children are not things to be molded, but are people to be unfolded. — Jess Lair"></amp-img>
        </p>
        <span class="h5">"Each day of our lives we make deposits in the memory banks of our children."
<br>
<span class="author">&mdash; Charles R. Swindoll, Evangelical Christian pastor</span>
        <br>
        <br> "It is easier to build strong children than to repair broken men."
        <br>
        <span class="author">&mdash; Frederick Douglass, abolitionist and statesman</span>
        <br>
        <br> "Children need models rather than critics."
        <br>
        <span class="author">&mdash; Joseph Joubert, French moralist</span></span>
        <p>
            <amp-img layout="responsive" width="550" height="368" src="/Images/children-need-mentors-quotes.jpg" class="paper" alt="An adult Ethiopian man sitting in a doorway talks to a young boy." title="Children need models rather than critics. — Joseph Joubert"></amp-img>
        </p>
        <br>
        <span class="h5">"Every child you encounter is a divine appointment."
<br>
<span class="author">&mdash; Wess Stafford, President Emeritus of Compassion International</span></span>
        <p>
            <a href="/letter-writing/the-power-of-words.htm">
                <amp-img layout="responsive" width="228" height="338" src="/Images/the-power-of-words-fertile-spirit-225-338.jpg" class="paper" alt="A young boy in glasses stands in front of a blue door" title="Our words quickly take root in the fertile soil of a child’s spirit."></amp-img>
            </a>
        </p>
        <blockquote><a href="/letter-writing/the-power-of-words.htm">The power of words</a> is that a life can be launched with as little as a single phrase, an uplifting word or an act of kindness.
            <br>
            <br> Think of the power we wield and the impact we can make if we become more intentional about encouraging our children.
            <br>
            <br> Our words are often the very things that help create future dreams. And sometimes those dreams are to be just like us.</blockquote>
        <span class="h5">"Children are great imitators. So give them something great to imitate."
<br>
<span class="author">&mdash; Anonymous</span>
        <br>
        <br> "Children have never been very good at listening to their elders, but they have never failed to imitate them."
        <br>
        <span class="author">&mdash; James Baldwin, novelist and social critic</span>
        <br>
        <br> "Children are like wet cement whatever falls on them makes an impression."
        <br>
        <span class="author">&mdash; Haim Ginott, child psychologist</span>
        <br>
        <br> "A child is a beam of sunlight from the Infinite and Eternal, with possibilities of virtue and vice, but as yet unstained."
        <br>
        <span class="author">&mdash; Lyman Abbott, American Congregationalist minister</span>
        <br>
        <br> "Children are the hands by which we take hold of heaven."
        <br>
        <span class="author">&mdash; Henry Ward Beecher, reverend and social activist</span></span>
        <p>
            <amp-img layout="responsive" width="550" height="368" src="/Images/children-take-hold-of-heaven.jpg" class="paper" alt="Ethiopian children walking across a dirt field. A cross is in the background." title="Children are the hands by which we take hold of heaven. — Henry Ward Beecher"></amp-img>
        </p>

        <span class="h5">"The soul is healed by being with children."
<br>
<span class="author">&mdash; Fyodor Dostoyevsky, Russian novelist and philosopher</span>
        <br>
        <br> "Children make your life important."
        <br>
        <span class="author">&mdash; Erma Bombeck, American humorist</span>
        <br>
        <br> "You have to love your children unselfishly. That is hard. But it is the only way."
        <br>
        <span class="author">&mdash; Barbara Bush, Former First Lady of the United States</span></span>
        <p>
            <amp-img layout="responsive" width="550" height="368" src="/Images/love-your-children-unselfishly.jpg" class="paper" alt="A Kenyan father holds his smiling infant daughter" title="You have to love your children unselfishly. That is hard. But it is the only way. — Barbara Bush"></amp-img>
        </p>

        <span class="h5">"The potential possibilities of any child are the most intriguing and stimulating in all creation."
<br>
<span class="author">&mdash; Ray L. Wilbur, third president of Stanford University</span>
        <br>
        <br> "Children are our most valuable resource."
        <br>
        <span class="author">&mdash; Herbert Hoover, 31st President of the United States</span>
        <br>
        <br> "Children are one third of our population and all of our future."
        <br>
        <span class="author">&mdash; Select Panel for the Promotion of Child Health, 1981</span>
        <br>
        <br> "Children are the living messages we send to a time we will not see."
        <br>
        <span class="author">&mdash; John F. Kennedy, 35th President of the United States</span></span>
        <p>
            <amp-img layout="responsive" width="550" height="368" src="/Images/bolivian-girl-rosy-cheeks.jpg" class="paper" alt="A Bolivian girl with rosy cheeks and a blue hat" title="Children are the living messages we send to a time we will not see. — John F. Kennedy"></amp-img>
        </p>

        <span class="h5">"You can learn many things from children. How much patience you have, for instance."
<br>
<span class="author">&mdash; Franklin P. Jones, American humorist</span>
        <br>
        <br> "Children see magic because they look for it."
        <br>
        <span class="author">&mdash; Christopher Moore, writer</span>
        <br>
        <br> "Only where children gather is there any real chance of fun."
        <br>
        <span class="author">&mdash; Mignon McLaughlin, journalist and author</span></span>
        <p>
            <amp-img layout="responsive" width="550" height="368" src="/Images/filipino-children-running-having-fun.jpg" class="paper" alt="Several Filipino children running through palm trees" title="Only where children gather is there any real chance of fun. — Mignon McLaughlin"></amp-img>
        </p>

        <span class="h5">"Every child comes with the message that God is not yet discouraged of man."
<br>
<span class="author">&mdash; Rabindranath Tagore, Bengali polymath</span>
        <br>
        <br> "A baby is God's opinion that the world should go on."
        <br>
        <span class="author">&mdash; Carl Sandburg, American poet</span>
        <br>
        <br> "If I could relive my life, I would devote my entire ministry to reaching children for God!"
        <br>
        <span class="author">&mdash; Dwight L. Moody, evangelist</span></span>
        <p>
            <amp-img layout="responsive" width="550" height="368" src="/Images/filipino-children-jumping-in-air.jpg" class="paper" alt="Four Filipino children jumping in the air in front of a church" title="If I could relive my life, I would devote my entire ministry to reaching children for God! — Dwight L. Moody"></amp-img>
        </p>

        <span class="h5">"The best way to make children good is to make them happy."
<br>
<span class="author">&mdash; Oscar Wilde, author and poet</span>
        <br>
        <br> "While we try to teach our children all about life, Our children teach us what life is all about."
        <br>
        <span class="author">&mdash; Angela Schwindt, home schooling mom</span>
        <br>
        <br> "Hugs can do great amounts of good, especially for children."
        <br>
        <span class="author">&mdash; Diana, Princess of Wales</span></span>
        <p>
            <amp-img layout="responsive" width="550" height="368" src="/Images/hugs-do-great-good.jpg" class="paper" alt="Two young Brazilian girls hug one another" title="Hugs can do great amounts of good, especially for children. — Diana, Princess of Wales"></amp-img>
        </p>

        <span class="h5">"Pretty much all the honest truth telling there is in the world is done by children."
<br>
<span class="author">&mdash; Oliver Wendell Holmes, author and poet</span>
        <br>
        <br> "Children seldom misquote. In fact, they usually repeat word for word what you shouldn't have said."
        <br>
        <span class="author">&mdash; Author unknown</span>
        <br>
        <br> "Don't worry that children never listen to you; worry that they are always watching you."
        <br>
        <span class="author">&mdash; Robert Fulghum, author</span></span>
        <p>
            <amp-img layout="responsive" width="550" height="368" src="/Images/child-watching-over-fence.jpg" class="paper" alt="A young Tanzanian boy wearing a red jacket is peering over a fence that is built near rusty corrugated metal siding" title="Don't worry that children never listen to you; worry that they are always watching you. — Robert Fulghum"></amp-img>
        </p>

        <span class="h5">"Old men can make war, but it is children who will make history."

<br>
            <span class="author">&mdash; Ray Merritt, author</span></span>
        <br>
        <br>
        <span class="h5">"Anyone who does anything to help a child is a hero to me."
<br>
<span class="author">&mdash; Fred Rogers, television personality</span>
        <br>
        <br> "When I approach a child, he inspires in me two sentiments — tenderness for what he is and respect for what he may become."
        <br>
        <span class="author">&mdash; Louis Pasteur, French chemist and microbiologist</span>
        <br>
        <br> "A child is a curly dimpled lunatic."
        <br>
        <span class="author">&mdash; Ralph Waldo Emerson, poet</span></span>
        <p>
            <amp-img layout="responsive" width="550" height="368" src="/Images/curly-dimpled-lunatic-famous-quotes-children.jpg" class="paper" alt="A young curly-haired Ecuadorian girl laughing " title="A child is a curly dimpled lunatic. — Ralph Waldo Emerson"></amp-img>
        </p>
        <span class="h5">"Children are a great comfort to us in our old age, and they help us reach it faster too."
<br>
<span class="author">&mdash; Author unknown</span>
        <br>
        <br> "If you want your children to be intelligent, read them fairy tales. If you want them to be more intelligent, read them more fairy tales."
        <br>
        <span class="author">&mdash; Albert Einstein, theoretical physicist</span>
        <br>
        <br> "A characteristic of the normal child is he doesn't act that way very often."
        <br>
        <span class="author">&mdash; Author unknown</span>
        <br>
        <br> "Play is often talked about as if it were a relief from serious learning. But for children play is serious learning. Play is really the work of childhood."
        <br>
        <span class="author">&mdash; Fred Rogers, television personality</span></span>
        <p>
            <amp-img layout="responsive" width="550" height="368" src="/Images/normal-children-famous-quotes.jpg" class="paper" alt="A group of Filipino children holding hands and jumping" title="A characteristic of the normal child is he doesn't act that way very often. — Author Unknown"></amp-img>
        </p>

        <span class="h5">"I have found the best way to give advice to your children is to find out what they want and then advise them to do it."
<br>
<span class="author">&mdash; Harry S. Truman, 33rd President of the United States</span>
        <br>
        <br> "The greatest gifts you can give your children are the roots of responsibility and the wings of independence."
        <br>
        <span class="author">&mdash; Denis Waitley, motivational speaker</span>
        <br>
        <br> "I continue to believe that if children are given the necessary tools to succeed, they will succeed beyond their wildest dreams!"
        <br>
        <span class="author">&mdash; David Vitter, Former U.S. Senator</span></span>
        <p>
            <amp-img layout="responsive" width="550" height="368" src="/Images/two-smiling-haitian-children.jpg" class="paper" alt="Two smiling Haitian boys" title="I continue to believe that if children are given the necessary tools to succeed, they will succeed beyond their wildest dreams! — David Vitter, U.S. senator"></amp-img>
        </p>
        <span class="h5">"Safety and security don't just happen, they are the result of collective consensus and public investment. We owe our children, the most vulnerable citizens in our society, a life free of violence and fear."
<br>
<span class="author">&mdash; Nelson Mandela, Former President of South Africa</span>
        <br>
        <br> "The best inheritance a parent can give his children is a few minutes of his time each day."
        <br>
        <span class="author">&mdash; Orlando Aloysius Battista, Canadia-American chemist and author</span>
        <br>
        <br> "If we are to teach real peace in this world, and if we are to carry on a real war against war, we shall have to begin with the children."
        <br>
        <span class="author">&mdash; Mahatma Gandhi, Indian political and spiritual leader</span>
        <br>
        <br> "It's the greatest poverty to decide that a child must die so that you may live as you wish."
        <br>
        <span class="author">&mdash; Mother Teresa, Roman Catholic nun</span>
        <br>
        <br> "Always kiss your children goodnight, even if they're already asleep."
        <br>
        <span class="author">&mdash; H. Jackson Brown, Jr., author</span></span>

